{
  "doc_id": "23227",
  "text": "Remark. In [CITATION_1] the authors however show that all the elements of HP(L) are unipotent and thus stabilise a finite subseries. The proof of this is quite tricky and delicate. Using this result and a classic result of Gruenberg [CITATION_2] , that tells us that any finitely generated Engel group is nilpotent, it is not difficult to obtain the following generalisation: if H is a finitely generated subgroup of HP(L), then there exists a positive integer m such that [V, m H] = 0. In particular H stabilises the finite series S = {[V, k H] : 0 ≤ k ≤ m}. We will do this in Section 2.",
